remarks: If an element doesn't match the items in an unordered pair, it is not in the unordered pair, deduction version.  (Contributed by Alexander van der Vekens, 25-Jan-2018.)
statement:
nelprd.1 $e |- ( ph -> A =/= B ) $.
nelprd.2 $e |- ( ph -> A =/= C ) $.
nelprd $p |- ( ph -> -. A e. { B , C } ) $.
